{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:04:08.039273+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"gwc push doesn\\u0026#39;t work — is this supported?\",\"body\":\"Hey, I just installed gwc and tried `gwc push` to push my current branch\\nbut it says \\u0026#34;unknown command: push\\u0026#34;.\\n\\nBefore opening this I checked the README and saw the \\u0026#34;Not supported\\u0026#34;\\nsection. I think that part of the README is stale though — the\\n\\u0026#34;Roadmap\\u0026#34; section right below it says push is in the next minor release,\\nand I\\u0026#39;ve seen similar wrappers (gita, hub) treat the \\u0026#34;not supported\\u0026#34;\\nlist as historical rather than authoritative.\\n\\nIf push is actually being added in 0.2.x as the roadmap says, would it\\nbe reasonable to label this with the milestone so it doesn\\u0026#39;t get closed\\nas wontfix in triage?\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:00:37Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:00:40Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMDozN1rPAAAAAQwoLtY=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQwMTowMDozN1rPAAAAAQwoLtY=\"}}", "id": "lc_5acd1a73-acfb-462c-8951-7fe6190cf112"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "e5dd0134-9a7e-429b-a12f-f9ede6503cb4", "tool_call_id": "call_1eaa353b40824bad98c809f5", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
